findings.recommendation:
Wrap in a try/catch and emit the snackbar on failure:
```kotlin
private fun Context.openAppSettings() {
    val intent = Intent(Settings.ACTION_APPLICATION_DETAILS_SETTINGS).apply {
        data = Uri.fromParts("package", packageName, null)
        addFlags(Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK)
    }
    runCatching { startActivity(intent) }
}
```
Silent no-op is acceptable — the user already saw the denial snackbar; a crash is the only wrong outcome.

Acceptable as implemented under D27. If the 200-char cap ever needs to shrink further for camera specifically, sanitize at the VM layer before calling `errorLog.e`:
```kotlin
fun reportCameraError(description: String, cause: Throwable?) {
    val safeCause = cause?.let { RuntimeException(it::class.simpleName) }
    viewModelScope.launch { errorLog.e("camera", description, safeCause) }
    _snackbar.tryEmit(R.string.camera_init_failed)
}
```
No change required now — documenting the decision trail.
